The spray will also be used in the Champions League and Europa League, but the Football League will trial it for one season in the Johnstone’s Paint Trophy.The FA, meanwhile, are expected to submit a proposal to the FA Cup committee for its use in the competition.

The spray will make its Premier League debut when Manchester United take on Swansea City on August 16.

The Premier League’s announcement over Twitter that it will be used this season was their most retweeted message to date, with over 10,000 retweets.

